_meta_time','1444145909'),(1654,68,'_wp_trash_meta_status','publish'),(1655,68,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1444145911'),(1656,66,'_wp_trash_meta_status','publish'),(1657,66,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1444145912'),(1658,64,'_wp_trash_meta_status','publish'),(1659,64,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1444145914'),(1660,1,'_wp_trash_meta_status','publish'),(1661,1,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1444145915'),(1662,1,'_wp_trash_meta_comments_status','a:1:{i:1;s:1:\"1\";}'),(1663,79,'_wp_trash_meta_status','publish'),(1664,79,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1444145918'),(1665,81,'_wp_trash_meta_status','publish'),(1666,81,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1444145940'),(1673,261,'header_image','198'),(1674,261,'_header_image','field_560bb9af7ac4d'),(1675,261,'intro_text','Lets be honest, people are never going to get excited when you use terms like learning management system or virtual learning environment. As organisations continue to reduce face-to-face training, we have to be more innovative in our approach to digital learning content. The best way to do this is to think about the wider digital landscape and how people use the internet in their own time.'),(1676,261,'_intro_text','field_560ba1b2a1f36'),(1677,261,'image_1',''),(1678,261,'_image_1','field_560ba235a1f37'),(1679,261,'image_2',''),(1680,261,'_image_2','field_560ba25da1f38'),(1681,261,'image_3',''),(1682,261,'_image_3','field_560ba272a1f39'),(1683,261,'image_4',''),(1684,261,'_image_4','field_560ba279a1f3a'),(1685,261,'main_body_of_text','By 2017 74% of all internet traffic will be video. People are more excited about watching video or animations than sifting through huge amounts of static content. Gone are the days when low bandwidth and connection problems were an issue when getting online. So why are so many digital learning programmes taking such a minimalist approach to visual and animated assets?\r\n \r\nThere are a number of reasons for this. In part, we still have to contend with onerous technical requirements including content management systems not designed for the types of websites being created and business assurance content that must be tracked for legal reasons. \r\n\r\nSo why isnt happening?\r\n\r\nAgencies and big companies are afraid to experiment when it comes to departing radically from the way content has been deployed over the last two decades. But we have to accept that what was once revolutionary is now old hat. User experience has come a long way and what was acceptable 15 years ago doesnt provide an optimum experience today.\r\n \r\nA core area of Tilts business is focused around online learning experiences and changing attitudes toward how people assimilate information online. In recent years we have been at the forefront of a marked shift away from traditional e-learning  solutions towards the creation of portals which host dynamic content in ways that emulate end-users typical internet experiences outside of the workplace.\r\n \r\nThe rationale for this is simple: if we pay attention to the way people choose to engage with content in their own time, we are more likely to get a higher uptake, and higher level of engagement, when we deploy content that aims to improve organisational effectiveness or productivity. We believe this change in direction is a positive, and permanent, one. It will, in time, come to replace the large-scale deployment of e-learning courses, particularly with regard to higher-level learning, soft skills and blended training-programmes.\r\n\r\nThe question that organisations, and their suppliers now face is how to increase the effectiveness of these portals and microsites. In many respects, the solutions deployed to date are still inferior to external sites that are available to our target audiences. The Internet is innovating exponentially and it wont be long before many of these portals begin to show signs of age. Users will be reminded of the difference between internal digital training and what they typically experience on the internet. There is a risk that they will feel coerced into learning rather than truly engaging with the content. The question that organisations, and their suppliers, now face is how to increase the effectiveness of these portals and microsites. Organisations may well ask whether there is a need to take further risk, at Tilt, we believe it is not only desirable, but absolutely essential, to innovate. '),(1686,261,'_main_body_of_text','field_560ba292a1f3b'),(1687,261,'image_5',''),(1688,261,'_image_5','field_560ba32ea1f3c'),(1689,261,'_','field_560bb9ca7ac4e'),(1692,262,'header_image','170'),(1693,262,'_header_image','field_560bb9af7ac4d'),(1694,262,'intro_text','We developed a series of advanced HTML5 games for Earth A New Wild, a new series currently airing on American television network PBS. Produced by National Geographic and Passion Planet, the series takes a fresh look at humankinds relationship to the planets wildest places and most fascinating species.'),(1695,262,'_intro_text','field_560ba1b2a1f36'),(1696,262,'image_1','238'),(1697,262,'_image_1','field_560ba235a1f37'),(1698,262,'image_2','239'),(1699,262,'_image_2','field_560ba25da1f38'),(1700,262,'image_3','240'),(1701,262,'_image_3','field_560ba272a1f39'),(1702,262,'image_4','241'),(1703,262,'_image_4','field_560ba279a1f3a'),(1704,262,'main_body_of_text','Tilt have created a new microsite which is inspired by content from the series. The Ecosystem Explorer is a collection of videos, games, and infographics designed to take students deep into the ecosystems of three thrilling animals: vultures, wolves, and sharks.\r\n\r\nRelated videos introduce each ecosystem and explore the relationship between animals and humans which is often more complicated than we realize. The microsite has been developed to encourage students to discover more about the ecology and conservation of these three worlds by exploring games, videos and infographics.\r\n\r\nBuilt using Create JS, Tilt showcased their advanced knowledge of HTML5 to take the project beyond the Flash requirements of the brief to an exciting new level. Tilt also developed dynamic illustrations for the games which were enhanced by suitably graphic sound effects!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.pbslearningmedia.org/resource/5aeed659-7f0b-417f-81d9-5f2e9c747644/ecosystem-explorer-earth-a-new-wild/\" target=\"_blank\">Experience it for yourself.</a>'),(1705,262,'_main_body_of_text','field_560ba292a1f3b'),(1706,262,'image_5','247'),(1707,262,'_image_5','field_560ba32ea1f3c'),(1708,262,'_','field_560bb9ca7ac4e'),(1711,263,'header_image','175'),(1712,263,'_header_image','field_560bb9af7ac4d'),(1713,263,'intro_text','Throughout the course of the year select members of the Tilt team have been battling the elements in an attempt to build up the stamina required to face the Tough Mudder challenge. '),(1714,263,'_intro_text','field_560ba1b2a1f36'),(1715,263,'image_1','224'),(1716,263,'_image_1','field_560ba235a1f37'),(1717,263,'image_2','225'),(1718,263,'_image_2','field_560ba25da1f38'),(1719,263,'image_3','226'),(1720,263,'_image_3','field_560ba272a1f39'),(1721,263,'image_4','227'),(1722,263,'_image_4','field_560ba279a1f3a'),(1723,263,'main_body_of_text','Tough Mudder is a team-oriented 10-12 mile (18-20 km) obstacle course designed to test physical strength and mental grit. Putting Camaraderie over finisher rankings this event allows participants to experience world class obstacles. Well this is what the events site said, but to be perfectly honest with you, we all just fancied the chance to get really really muddy! Whats not to like? Check out our <a href=\"https://vimeo.com/130366057\" target=\"_blank\">training video</a> . . . if you can call it training!\r\n\r\nThe course took a little over 3 hours, with some great new obstacles introduced by the Tough Mudder team. Our favorites were <a href=\"https://toughmudder.co.uk/obstacles/king-swingers\" target=\"_blank\">King of the Swingers</a> and  <a href=\"https://toughmudder.co.uk/content/mud-mile-20\" target=\"_blank\">Mud Mile</a>, with the latter seeing our very own Stig Coldham fall head first into waist deep mud and emerge covered in more mud that Arnold Schwarzenegger in the end scene from Predator. \r\n\r\nSee you in 2016 Tough Mudder. Anyone up for a challenge?'),(1724,263,'_main_body_of_text','field_560ba292a1f3b'),(1725,263,'image_5',''),(1726,263,'_image_5','field_560ba32ea1f3c'),(1727,263,'_','field_560bb9ca7ac4e'),(1730,264,'header_image','190'),(1731,264,'_header_image','field_560bb9af7ac4d'),(1732,264,'intro_text','Codebar is a non-profit initiative that facilitates the growth of a diverse tech community by running regular programming workshops. It has grown from a bi-weekly meet-up with a handful of enthusiastic learners to a weekly event with ever-increasing numbers. '),(1733,264,'_intro_text','field_560ba1b2a1f36'),(1734,264,'image_1','251'),(1735,264,'_image_1','field_560ba235a1f37'),(1736,264,'image_2','252'),(1737,264,'_image_2','field_560ba25da1f38'),(1738,264,'image_3','253'),(1739,264,'_image_3','field_560ba272a1f39'),(1740,264,'image_4','254'),(1741,264,'_image_4','field_560ba279a1f3a'),(1742,264,'main_body_of_text','It has grown from a bi-weekly meet-up with a handful of enthusiastic learners to a weekly event with ever-increasing numbers. We have been delighted to welcome Codebar into our offices throughout the course of 2015. Sarah, Rachel and Miles have been advocates of the events and have really driven Tilts involvement. The relaxed format of the workshops allows for a great mix of networking, collaboration and mentoring. Were really pleased to be involved and look forward to playing hosts again soon. \r\n\r\nThis is a fantastic initiative, <a href=\"http://codebar.io/\" target=\"_blank\">get involved</a>!\r\n'),(1743,264,'_main_body_of_text','field_560ba292a1f3b'),(1744,264,'image_5',''),(1745,264,'_image_5','field_560ba32ea1f3c'),(1746,264,'_','field_560bb9ca7ac4e'),(1749,265,'header_image','198'),(1750,265,'_header_image','field_560bb9af7ac4d'),(175